Operators  --> + - * / % etc. ** -- gives us the power of the digit. 2**3 gives us 8.
++ , -- , 
Precedence = Parenthesis --> ** (exponents) --> * / % --> + - -- Highest on the left side. 
IF operators of similar precedence given then solve then from the left side.

Taking UserInput --> Default for user input is String from the window promt.
let username = window.prompt("Enter the username?");

* or create a html button and take input from there.
HTML part -->
     <h1 id="UserH1"></h1>
    <label>Username</label>
    <input id="UserInput"><br><br>
    <button id="UserSubmit">Submit</button>
JS part -->
	document.getElementById("UserSubmit").onclick = function(){
		username =  document.getElementById("UserInput").value;
		document.getElementById("UserH1").textContent = `Hello ${username}`;
	}

Typeconversion in JS -->
x = String(x);
y = Number(y);
z = Boolean(z); // Gives true if theres any value given
--> String can be converted to boolean to check if its empty or not. If string is empty then on converting to boolean it returns false else itreturns true. 

On trying to type convert anundefined variable to number -- returns NaN.
On trying to type convert anundefined variable to boolean -- returns false.
On trying to type convert anundefined variable to string -- returns undefined.

CONST --> making a variable const makes sure that  it cannot be changed after that or js gives us a error.
